<treatment id="03E66827B670FFC9FF50B6FD5155FE96" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03E66827B670FFC9FF50B6FD5155FE96" httpUri="http://treatment.plazi.org/id/03E66827B670FFC9FF50B6FD5155FE96" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB670FFCAFF50B6FD5643F87D" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B670FFCAFF50B6FD5493F8CD" blockId="17.[136,1452,1747,1810]" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">
<heading id="D0B86E5DB670FFCAFF50B6FD5493F8CD" bold="true" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFF50B6FD5493F8CD" bold="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFF50B6FD5514F931" box="[136,377,1747,1774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFF50B6FD5514F931" bold="true" box="[136,377,1747,1774]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">Atraphaxis davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFE67B6FA5604F931" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[447,617,1747,1774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFE67B6FA5604F931" bold="true" box="[447,617,1747,1774]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Russian Transbaikalia are not related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFB1BB6FA5126F931" authorityName="Jaub. &amp; Spach" authorityYear="1844" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[1219,1355,1748,1774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pungens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFB1BB6FA5126F931" bold="true" box="[1219,1355,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. pungens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFA4AB6FA5493F8CD" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFA4AB6FA5493F8CD" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B670FFCAFF50B76E5643F87D" blockId="17.[136,1451,1856,2062]" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">
The results of Maximum Likelihood (ML) and Bayesian analyses (BI) applied for the combined 3-plastid loci clearly demonstrate that the plants from Russian Transbaikalia are not related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFC03B74A5037F8A1" authorityName="Jaub. &amp; Spach" authorityYear="1844" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[987,1114,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pungens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFC03B74A5037F8A1" box="[987,1114,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. pungens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFB5EB74A5177F8A1" box="[1158,1306,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFB5EB74A5177F8A1" box="[1158,1306,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by maternal lineage and evolved autochthonously.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3558ABAB670FFC9FF65B7825155FE96" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="62" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B670FFCAFF65B7825501F7D1" blockId="17.[136,1451,1856,2062]" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">
Within the Transbaikalian subclade, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFDB1B782569DF819" box="[617,752,1964,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFDB1B782569DF819" box="[617,752,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFCF7B78257BFF819" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[815,978,1964,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B670FFCAFCF7B78257BFF819" box="[815,978,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="61">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B670FFCAFC05B7825024F818" box="[989,1097,1964,1991]" form="two" pageId="17" pageNumber="61" rank="form">form two</taxonomicName>
well supported subclades and demonstrate clear distinctions in the morphology of their life form, leaf blades, generative shoots and thyrses, ochreas, perianths and styles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B673FFC9FF65B0B056E2FF02" blockId="18.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">
Perianth morphology of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FE3CB0B156E7FF67" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[484,650,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FE3CB0B156E7FF67" box="[484,650,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FCABB0B1506EFF67" box="[883,1027,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bracteata">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FCABB0B1506EFF67" box="[883,1027,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. bracteata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is the main characteristic that differentiates 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FEFAB0ED55ACFF03" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[290,449,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FEFAB0ED55ACFF03" box="[290,449,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FDDDB0ED56E5FF03" box="[517,648,194,221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FDDDB0ED56E5FF03" box="[517,648,194,221]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF0D931B673FFC9FF65B0C85155FE96" blockId="18.[136,1452,158,329]" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FF65B0C855CBFEDF" box="[189,422,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FF65B0C855CBFEDF" box="[189,422,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">Atraphaxis davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FE3AB0C956E9FEDF" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[482,644,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FE3AB0C956E9FEDF" box="[482,644,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FCCEB0C957F8FEDF" authorityName="Jaub. &amp; Spach" authorityYear="1844" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[790,917,231,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pungens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FCCEB0C957F8FEDF" box="[790,917,231,257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. pungens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FC0AB0C9500BFEDF" box="[978,1126,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FC0AB0C9500BFEDF" box="[978,1126,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with longer ochreas, longer styles, and minutely tuberculate fruit surface. 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FD4EB1245713FEFB" box="[662,894,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="davurica">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FD4EB1245713FEFB" box="[662,894,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">Atraphaxis davurica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has spongy stigmas, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FBACB1255178FEFB" authorityName="Yurtseva &amp; Badmaeva &amp; Mavrodiev" authorityYear="2021" box="[1140,1301,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="selengensis">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FBACB1255178FEFB" box="[1140,1301,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. selengensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has compact globular stigmas. The stigmas are spherical in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FD49B101574FFE97" box="[657,802,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="frutescens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FD49B101574FFE97" box="[657,802,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. frutescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and bent or slightly beveled out in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4FA2B2B673FFC9FB6DB101515CFE97" authorityName="Jaub. &amp; Spach" authorityYear="1844" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[1205,1329,303,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Polygonaceae" genus="Atraphaxis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="18" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pungens">
<emphasis id="B93B0523B673FFC9FB6DB101515CFE97" box="[1205,1329,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="62">A. pungens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
